This paper is primarily focused on using reinforcement learning to optimize code for neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper specifically mentions improving inference time for deep networks, which is a common application in computer vision (cs.CV) and augmented reality (cs.AR). Finally, the paper also discusses using domain-knowledge inspired logic, which could potentially fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
